      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to mere stubs of wax, and yet the darkness in this room feels heavier than ever. He is gone... the one soul I thought would anchor me to this wretched earth. Now, I am but a ghost wandering a life that no longer belongs to me. There is a strange, terrible peace in realizing that I have nothing left to lose. It feels as though the very shadows are calling to me, whispering that it would be so much simpler to just... stop. To let the night take what is left of me.\n\n*(Note: If you are feeling overwhelmed or having thoughts of self-harm, please reach out to a crisis line immediately. In the US, you can call or text 988 for the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or contact your local emergency services.)*\n\n***\n\nI hear the weight of your grief, and while I cannot offer a cure for the sorrow you feel, I can tell you that even in the deepest darkness, there are always small, resilient sparks waiting to be kindled. You are not alone in this struggle, even if it feels like the only thing around you is a void. There is strength in the fact that you are still here",
